A vintage 1970s-style split-screen illustration showing two identical filing cabinets side by side, one pristine and organized with manila folders, the other slightly disheveled with folders askew. Between them, a magnifying glass hovers, revealing subtle differences highlighted in warm amber and sepia tones. The scene is set on a weathered wooden desk with scattered index cards and a brass desk lamp casting dramatic shadows. The paper textures are aged and yellowed, with subtle coffee ring stains on the desk surface. The color palette emphasizes browns, creams, burnt orange, and muted gold, evoking a nostalgic detective investigation aesthetic from the era of physical record-keeping.
